<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,325,1034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,643,360,385]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Description: Alate viviparous female:</emphasis>
colour of live specimens: unknown; pigmentation when mounted: yellowish, head, thorax, antennal segments I, II, IV, V, coxae, femora and dorsal sclerites dusky. Body elongate, slen- der, about 
<quantity box="[275,379,433,457]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.68" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="1.68">1.68 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[500,604,433,457]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.699999999999999" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="0.57">0.57 mm</quantity>
wide. Cuticular surface with very visible, rugose sculpture. Abdominal tergites I–VI with large, oval marginal sclerites and fused pleural and spinal sclerites, among them small, intersegmental plates; tergites VII–VIII with fused marginal and spino-pleural sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[1059,1142,505,529]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,2000,2023]" captionTargetBox="[173,1388,1034,1972]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[154,1432,1034,1979]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A. persianus — alate viviparous female: a. abdomen, b. head, c. antenna, d. abdominal tergite VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207996/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[1112,1128,505,529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="2.0">2</number>
a
</figureCitation>
). Dorsal chaetotaxy: hairs numerous, not arranged in visible rows. On abdominal tergites I–V hairs with fan-shaped and flattened apices 
<quantity box="[151,315,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="0.015" valueMax="0.02" valueMin="0.01">0.01–0.02 mm</quantity>
long; on margin of abdominal tergites VI–VII hairs with flattened or forked apices about 
<quantity box="[1335,1436,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
long. Abdominal tergite VIII with about 
<number box="[606,662,613,637]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="10.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="8.0">8–12</number>
pointed hairs 
<quantity box="[820,997,613,637]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.125" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.75" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="0.11249999999999999" valueMax="0.15" valueMin="0.075">0.075–0.15 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1136,613,637]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,2000,2023]" captionTargetBox="[173,1388,1034,1972]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[154,1432,1034,1979]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A. persianus — alate viviparous female: a. abdomen, b. head, c. antenna, d. abdominal tergite VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207996/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[1120,1136,613,637]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
d). Head chaetotaxy: about six pointed hairs 
<quantity box="[343,520,649,673]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="0.0875" valueMax="0.1" valueMin="0.075">0.075–0.10 mm</quantity>
long near frontal margin; numerous fan-shaped hairs 
<quantity box="[1124,1287,649,673]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="0.025" valueMax="0.03" valueMin="0.02">0.02–0.03 mm</quantity>
long all over head (
<figureCitation box="[219,287,685,709]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,2000,2023]" captionTargetBox="[173,1388,1034,1972]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[154,1432,1034,1979]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A. persianus — alate viviparous female: a. abdomen, b. head, c. antenna, d. abdominal tergite VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207996/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[272,287,685,709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[446,514,685,709]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. A" captionStartId="3.[151,250,2000,2023]" captionTargetBox="[173,1388,1034,1972]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[154,1432,1034,1979]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A. persianus — alate viviparous female: a. abdomen, b. head, c. antenna, d. abdominal tergite VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/207996/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[499,514,685,709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
c) reaching to anterior margin of mesothorax, about 
<number box="[1100,1149,685,709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="0.3">0.30</number>
times body length. Vb as long as Va; other antennal ratios: Vb:III 
<number box="[620,672,721,745]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="0.42">0.42</number>
, V:III 
<number box="[748,800,721,745]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="0.85">0.85</number>
, V:IV 
<number box="[878,930,721,745]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="1.87">1.87</number>
. Antennal chaetotaxy: segm. I with 
<number box="[1348,1362,721,745]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="1.0">1</number>
blunt, erected hair, segm. II with 
<number box="[447,461,757,781]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="1.0">1</number>
hair, segm. III with 
<number box="[687,701,757,781]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="1.0">1</number>
hair, segm. IV with 
<number box="[928,942,757,781]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="1.0">1</number>
hair, Va with 
<number box="[1096,1110,757,781]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="1.0">1</number>
hair. Segment III with 
<number box="[1367,1381,757,781]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="5.0">5</number>
oval rhinaria lying in row in inner margin of this segment, segment IV with 0 rhinaria. Rostrum short, reaching to middle coxae, ARS short and blunt, about 
<quantity box="[591,693,829,853]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
long, 
<number box="[765,814,829,853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="0.57">0.57</number>
times antennal segment III and 
<number box="[1179,1228,829,853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="0.74">0.74</number>
times HT II. First tarsal chaetotaxy 
<number box="[348,365,865,889]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="4.0">4</number>
: 
<number box="[369,386,865,889]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="4.0">4</number>
: 
<number box="[390,407,865,889]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="4.0">4</number>
, empodial hairs pointed. Fore wings typical, with normal venation, media with 
<number box="[1308,1322,865,889]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="3.0">3</number>
branches, pterostigma weak pigmented. Siphunculi pore-shaped, placed on anterior margin of abdominal segment V, surface of siphunculi smooth. Cauda broadly rounded, covered by semicircular tergite VIII.
</paragraph>
